          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-D"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Approximate to monoenergetic neutrons were",
                " produced through the D(d,n)3He reaction with a",
                " deuterium gas target 2.0 cm in length and 3.2-3.5 atm",
                " in pressure."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The two 64Zn samples were set back-to-back, it allows",
                " to registrate the forward (0. to 90.deg.) and",
                "  backward (90. to 180.deg.) alpha events at the same",
                "  time.",
                "The thickness of the Zn targets was 266.3 ug/cm2 and",
                " the mass was 4.05 +- 0.05 mg for each sample.",
                "The abundance of 64Zn was 99.4%. Each sample was",
                " evaporated on a tantalum backing 4.8 cm in diameter",
                " and 50 um in thickness.",
                "For background measurement, there were two tantalum",
                " films back-to -back were used.",
                "A 238U fission foil was placed at the backward.",
                "The purity of the sample was 99.999%.",
                "The mass and the diameter of the sample were 7.85 +/-",
                " 0.10 mg."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The twin grid ionization chamber was",
                " constructed at Frank Laboratory of Neutron Physics,",
                " Dubna Russia."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A relatively calibrated BF3 long counter was",
                " used as a neutron flux monitor.",
                "The absolute neutron flux for 5.0 MeV was determined",
                " by counting the 238U fission fragments.",
                "The 238U(n,f) cross section was taken from the",
                " ENDF/B-VI library."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-SYS",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The scale errors come from:"
